eNCA's Nceba Ntlanganiso went to the town and filed this report. Courtesy #DStv403 KIRKWOOD, Eastern Cape - Hundreds of farmworkers in Sunday's River in the Eastern Cape have been protesting since Wednesday. They're demanding better working conditions and salary increases from R23 to R30 an hour. READ: Farmworkers demand better conditions The town has been shut down, and protesting workers say they won't back down until their demands are met. eNCA's Nceba Ntlanganiso went to the town and filed this report in the video above.